What you need to know:

Senegal head coach Aliou Cisse has made it a personal goal to lift the trophy having twice missed out in finals.The 45-year-old tasted defeat in a final, first as captain in 2002 -- he missed a penalty in the shootout defeat to Cameroon -- and then as coach in 2019."I want this Africa Cup of Nations. I have been running after it since 1999," he said last month after unveiling the squad.